Here’s the important part: in this repo, the move effect constant value is the script index.

Why:

The move stores .effect as an enum value in the move table, loaded from data.json.
The battle engine jumps to be_seq.narc using that value directly at battle_script.c:2312.
be_seq.narc is built from effect_script_files in listed order at res/battle/scripts/meson.build and res/battle/scripts/effects/meson.build:257.
So the mapping works like this:

BATTLE_EFFECT_HIT is value 0 -> effect_script_0000.s
value 1 -> effect_script_0001.s
value 259 -> effect_script_0259.s
How to add a new one:

Add a new effect script file with the next free number, not an already-used one.
Add that file to effects/meson.build.
Add a new BATTLE_EFFECT_* constant to generated/battle_move_effects.txt in the matching slot.
Set your move’s data.json "effect.type" to that new constant.
Example:

If your new script is effect_script_0296.s
Add BATTLE_EFFECT_PLASMA_BURST as the next entry after BATTLE_EFFECT_VENOSHOCK in generated/battle_move_effects.txt:295
Then in the move JSON:
"effect": {
  "type": "BATTLE_EFFECT_PLASMA_BURST",
  "chance": 0
}
Important correction:

effect_script_0259.s is not free in your repo.
generated/battle_move_effects.txt:260 is BATTLE_EFFECT_TRICK_ROOM, which means value 259 already maps to effect_script_0259.s.
So if you want a brand-new effect, do not reuse 0259 unless you mean to replace Trick Room’s behavior.

